                           <desc type="GuestText">Fragment of Revelation of John (Rev. 3:5-13).</desc>
                           <q xml:lang="gez"/>
                           
                           <note> Written on leaves originating from an older manuscript (15th
                              cent.?). </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1"><desc>In a few fols. the word qum "stop", "stand" (<locus target="#15rb">15rb</locus>, 28ra 48ra), frequently in abbreviated form (ቁ፡) by a crude
                           secondary hand, is written interlineally or in the margins throughout the
                           Ms.</desc></item>
                        
                        <item xml:id="e2"><locus target="#6r">6r</locus> <desc>Shelfmark C3-IV-233</desc></item>
                       
                        <item xml:id="e3"><locus target="#1r">1r</locus> <desc>Shelfmark 116</desc></item>
                        <item xml:id="e4"><desc>- The title is written on the front board with black
                           modern paint.</desc></item>
                        <item xml:id="e5"><desc>The internal number of the monastic library (116) is
                           written on <locus target="#1r">1r</locus>.</desc></item>
                        <item xml:id="e6"><desc>Numbers, partly
                           rubricated, are written by at least two different hands (?; cp. <locus target="#15r">15r</locus>, 28r; and <locus target="#32r">32r</locus>;
